1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:00,880 --> 00:00:03,160
(Previously) Why didn't
everyone else get paid, but I did?

3
00:00:04,040 --> 00:00:05,280
I'm the one who hired you.

4
00:00:07,560 --> 00:00:08,560
I like you, Rome.

5
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:10,880
If we do it in the car, would you mind?

6
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:13,439
Pete and I didn't do anything that night.

7
00:00:13,440 --> 00:00:14,440
It's nice though.

8
00:00:14,840 --> 00:00:16,000
Seeing you jealous.

9
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,600
We're not back together yet.

10
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,200
How many times do I have to tell you that?

11
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:24,120
You know why I have to do this.

12
00:00:24,680 --> 00:00:26,160
Can I stay over tonight?

13
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:29,360
So you can punish me however you want.

14
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,000
(Episode 7: Point of No Return)

15
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:42,200
I'm glad we're on good terms again.

16
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,200
Mm-hmm.

17
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:48,640
I'm still waiting if you want
us to get back together.

18
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:51,120
Give me some time.

19
00:01:02,160 --> 00:01:03,160
Hey.

20
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:06,240
I think I'll pick up where
Rome and I left off on this trip.

21
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:08,960
Mm.

22
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,640
If you like him that much, go for it.

23
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:20,720
Hey, I…

24
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:24,119
Guys! Listen up!

25
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:27,079
Before we head out,
let's take a group photo.

26
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:28,400
Come on. Off the bus.

27
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:29,800
Move it.

28
00:01:29,801 --> 00:01:32,399
Let's go.

29
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,680
Come on.

30
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:39,479
FINE ARTS OUTING
Camera's over there.

31
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:41,639
FINE ARTS OUTING
One, two, three!

32
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,000
FINE ARTS OUTING
Whoo!

33
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:52,200
"Only Friends: Dream On"

34
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,279
Gather round!

35
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:02,080
Grab your keys, everyone.

36
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,200
Stick to your assigned tents.

37
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:08,079
Some are for two, some for three.

38
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:10,039
[The sound of Fine Arts
students' displeasure]

39
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:10,720
What?

40
00:03:10,721 --> 00:03:13,839
And don't go switching tents
as you please, okay?

41
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:16,199
Come on, take your keys.

42
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,200
This one's yours. This is yours.
And this is yours.

43
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,120
This one's yours.

44
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,400
This one's yours.

45
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,879
Gosh, I'm having a headache.

46
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,680
Timmy, a word?

47
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:25,880
What?

48
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,440
What is it?

49
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:33,919
Why is there not enough room this year?

50
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:34,920
We're cramming people in.

51
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:38,880
Last time, it was two per tent.

52
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:42,080
This is the budget we've got.

53
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,160
Hold on.

54
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,400
Didn't we already get sponsor funding?

55
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,936
If we're really short on money,
we shouldn't have gone on this trip.

56
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,440
We should've saved it for the play.

57
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,239
No way.

58
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,600
Food, drinks, and trips are essential.

59
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:01,000
Besides, we do have enough money.

60
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,840
Someone just embezzled it.

61
00:04:03,979 --> 00:04:04,979
Huh?

62
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:08,400
Is someone stealing from the play budget?

63
00:04:08,793 --> 00:04:09,793
Um…

64
00:04:11,406 --> 00:04:12,846
I'm gathering evidence.

65
00:04:13,646 --> 00:04:14,886
Let me make sure first.

66
00:04:15,353 --> 00:04:16,473
I'll take care of it.

67
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,600
You just enjoy the trip.

68
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:23,000
Leave the headache to your producer.

69
00:04:29,999 --> 00:04:32,038
Hey, this one's for Jack and me.

70
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:33,143
Tua, that one is yours.

71
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,040
Who am I sharing with?

72
00:04:36,446 --> 00:04:37,446
Probably Timmy.

73
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,840
Where is he, anyway? Why isn't he here?

74
00:04:41,053 --> 00:04:42,813
I think he's sorting out
the accommodations.

75
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,320
Yeah?
Hey, Arnold.

76
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,320
Which tent are you in?

77
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,160
This one, I think.

78
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,440
Good.

79
00:05:05,679 --> 00:05:06,679
We're neighbors.

80
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:09,400
Dean.

81
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,560
Hm?

82
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,800
Can we switch?

83
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,000
I want to talk to Jack about the script.

84
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,760
Besides, I'm not sure
I want to play the role anymore.

85
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:23,320
Hey. Is it really that bad?

86
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:27,120
Arnold, let's talk later.

87
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,480
You can share my tent.

88
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,320
If he stops talking to me completely…

89
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,160
I don't think I can handle it.

90
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,680
Well, well.

91
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,240
What a coincidence.

92
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,440
We're sharing a tent.

93
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:15,040
Did you plan this, hon?

94
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,080
Hey, Rome.

95
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,480
You're in this tent too?

96
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:24,880
Mm.

97
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:30,080
But I can move to another tent,
so you guys can be more comfortable.

98
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,160
Uh… hey.

99
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:34,160
You can stay here with us.

100
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,680
The more, the merrier.

101
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:40,560
Besides, I think the other tents are full.

102
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:49,800
Yeah, just crash here.

103
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,680
No one's going to do anything to you.

104
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,400
Unless…

105
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,920
you're planning to do
something to my friend.

106
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,920
Hey, Raffy.

107
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,480
What are you saying?
You're going to scare Rome off.

108
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:07,840
He's not scared.

109
00:07:08,760 --> 00:07:09,760
He likes it.

110
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:19,400
Fine. I'll stay.

111
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,400
Hey.

112
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,120
He's not going to quit.

113
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:48,320
Jack will talk him out of it.

114
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:52,800
You know what?
He's not saying a word to me.

115
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,360
He doesn't read my messages.

116
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,200
Nothing at all.

117
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,280
I really messed up.

118
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:02,800
Come on. He's not going to
let your friendship end like that.

119
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,960
Look at Jack and me.

120
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:09,240
We had a huge fight,
but we ended up talking again.

121
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:14,240
I think Arnold might
give you another chance.

122
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:17,000
But you guys are ex-boyfriends.

123
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:20,200
You've been connected for so long,
you can't just cut ties completely.

124
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:22,760
But I'm just…

125
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:28,760
just a faculty friend who helps him out.

126
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,240
Exactly.

127
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,600
You've always been there for him.

128
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,200
And this time, you helped him too.

129
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:39,960
Even if your method… was money.

130
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:42,840
Sugar daddy much?

131
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,520
You'd be mad too if you were him, right?

132
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:52,840
I think the real reason
he's upset is that you lied to him.

133
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:56,560
Hey, Tua.

134
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:02,600
After every content shoot
with him on this trip, I'll whisper,

135
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:08,720
"Arnold, Tua loves you so much.
Please give your sugar daddy a chance."

136
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:12,280
"Next time, sugar daddy Tua
will pay even more."

137
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,480
When you said you'd quit earlier,

138
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:37,440
were you serious or
just trying to hurt Tua?

139
00:09:40,613 --> 00:09:41,653
Don't worry, Jack.

140
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:45,560
I know how important this project is to you

141
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,120
and to everyone in the faculty.

142
00:09:51,273 --> 00:09:53,433
I won't let my personal issues
affect the work.

143
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:03,720
Saying that means you care about Tua a lot.

144
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:09,920
I've known Tua for four years.

145
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:14,080
He's the best person I know.

146
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,840
And he means no harm to anyone.

147
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,240
I think you know that too.

148
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:25,520
When I was falling apart because of Dean,
he was the one who helped me.

149
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:28,920
I get it, Arnold.

150
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:34,200
The way he handled it was foul.

151
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:40,720
But you can just tell
him not to do it again.

152
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:47,960
Try to see his intention.
See why he did it.

153
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,080
Arnold…

154
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:55,040
you're more capable than you think.

155
00:10:58,073 --> 00:10:59,833
You got me the lead actor I really wanted.

156
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:04,040
And the person who made you realize that…

157
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,120
is the one who paid you.

158
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:20,600
I just don't like liars.

159
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:23,480
Sincerity is the first
step in any relationship.

160
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,960
I don't know what else
he'll lie to me about.

161
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:20,839
Jack, don't you think
you've taken us a bit too far out?

162
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:24,520
If this thing tips over,
no one's coming to save us.

163
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:27,040
You know I can't swim well, right?

164
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,400
I can.

165
00:12:28,699 --> 00:12:30,939
Don't be scared. I've got you.

166
00:12:31,473 --> 00:12:32,473
Right.

167
00:12:33,959 --> 00:12:35,559
You're the smartest person in the world.

168
00:12:35,733 --> 00:12:38,493
You can swim, you can direct plays…

169
00:12:39,173 --> 00:12:40,773
Is there anything you're not good at?

170
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,340
There is.

171
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:46,260
I got an F.

172
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:47,900
Wait.

173
00:12:48,420 --> 00:12:50,739
When was it? I didn't know that.

174
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:51,740
What subject?

175
00:12:52,660 --> 00:12:53,980
Friendship 101.

176
00:12:55,220 --> 00:12:56,220
I failed.

177
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:00,820
Seriously?

178
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:08,300
I don't want to be your friend anymore.

179
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:11,940
I want to be your boyfriend.

180
00:13:13,740 --> 00:13:14,740
Wow.

181
00:13:15,940 --> 00:13:16,940
Just like that?

182
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:23,460
So you planned this kayaking
just to ask me to be your boyfriend?

183
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:25,420
This feels like a movie scene.

184
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,540
You're such a director.

185
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:31,340
So, what do you say?

186
00:13:32,460 --> 00:13:33,460
Yes or no?

187
00:13:39,740 --> 00:13:40,740
Okay.

188
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:45,180
But…

189
00:13:48,180 --> 00:13:51,540
I want to announce to everyone that I won.

190
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,180
What are you talking about?

191
00:13:55,260 --> 00:14:01,540
I bet Timmy and Tua
you'd be the one to ask first.

192
00:14:04,460 --> 00:14:07,579
Now they owe me drinks at Pink's bar.

193
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:09,300
Whoo!

194
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:14,100
So I just walked right into your trap?

195
00:14:15,060 --> 00:14:16,060
Yep.

196
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:22,859
Jack asked me to be his boyfriend!

197
00:14:22,860 --> 00:14:23,580
Yay!
Careful.

198
00:14:38,180 --> 00:14:39,380
What is this, a music video?

199
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:48,820
I'm waiting for you.

200
00:14:52,980 --> 00:14:54,180
Don't you miss our first year?

201
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:56,260
Yeah.

202
00:14:58,540 --> 00:15:00,100
When you asked me to be your boyfriend.

203
00:15:05,260 --> 00:15:06,300
Big mistake.

204
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:09,820
I should've smacked you
into the water with a paddle.

205
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:13,700
Oh please. You couldn't do it.
You were infatuated with me.

206
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:21,460
Want to go kayaking?

207
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:24,140
You hoping for something?

208
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:26,700
No.

209
00:15:28,220 --> 00:15:30,060
I just want to film some
content with you too.

210
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:34,780
Come on.

211
00:15:35,060 --> 00:15:36,060
Let's go.

212
00:16:19,220 --> 00:16:19,460
Ouch.

213
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:22,020
Damn it.

214
00:16:27,340 --> 00:16:28,700
Are you feeding the ants or what?

215
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:31,300
You've got red bite marks all over.

216
00:16:36,460 --> 00:16:38,660
I'll put something on them
when we get back to the tent.

217
00:16:49,740 --> 00:16:51,140
Please don't quit, Arnold.

218
00:16:53,620 --> 00:16:56,780
This is my fault. Don't let
everyone else suffer for it.

219
00:17:00,260 --> 00:17:01,460
What do you take me for?

220
00:17:12,340 --> 00:17:13,340
I'm not quitting.

221
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,580
This project helped me
discover another side of myself.

222
00:17:19,980 --> 00:17:23,740
I never thought I'd enjoy acting this much.

223
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:31,900
And I got to experience it…

224
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:34,740
because of you.

225
00:17:40,980 --> 00:17:42,700
But I'm still disappointed in you.

226
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:47,140
You lied to me.

227
00:17:52,140 --> 00:17:58,020
So from now on, whatever it is,
just be honest with me.

228
00:17:58,420 --> 00:18:00,220
If you need help with
anything, just tell me.

229
00:18:06,780 --> 00:18:07,780
Don't forget.

230
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:11,380
You and I…

231
00:18:13,140 --> 00:18:14,300
we're more than just friends.

232
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:21,980
Am I forgiven?

233
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:24,300
Of course.

234
00:18:26,820 --> 00:18:28,940
I can't stay mad at you for long.

235
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:33,260
You didn't talk to me at all.

236
00:18:34,460 --> 00:18:35,980
It was torture.

237
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:39,060
Hey, I had to act with nonchalance.

238
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:45,380
Come on. Stop looking so sad.

239
00:18:47,140 --> 00:18:49,180
I thought you'd never talk to me again.

240
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:53,860
Getting bitten by a whole nest of ants
hurts less than you ignoring my messages.

241
00:18:54,980 --> 00:18:55,980
No more of that.

242
00:18:56,380 --> 00:18:57,380
We're good now.

243
00:18:58,940 --> 00:18:59,940
Smile.

244
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:04,620
Come on, smile.

245
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:08,540
Let's go.

246
00:19:09,260 --> 00:19:10,260
Let's join the others.

247
00:19:21,580 --> 00:19:22,940
I just wanted to see him smile.

248
00:19:24,060 --> 00:19:25,620
It's better than that sad cat face.

249
00:19:29,220 --> 00:19:31,420
The wait for his forgiveness felt endless.

250
00:19:32,580 --> 00:19:35,860
I'm relieved now.
I won't make him angry again.

251
00:19:48,540 --> 00:19:49,540
Hey.

252
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:50,820
Wanna go for a swim?

253
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:54,460
No. It's too hot.

254
00:19:55,060 --> 00:19:56,060
Why don't you ask Pete?

255
00:19:58,740 --> 00:20:01,660
Hey, knock it off. That's not funny.

256
00:20:02,460 --> 00:20:03,540
I'm not into Pete.

257
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:10,180
He's crazy about you.

258
00:20:10,540 --> 00:20:11,860
Why not give him a chance?

259
00:20:16,060 --> 00:20:18,420
Think about yourself.
You chased me nonstop until I gave in.

260
00:20:20,940 --> 00:20:22,660
Now he's doing the same to you.

261
00:20:23,780 --> 00:20:25,980
You'll cave eventually.

262
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:30,740
Maybe I should find
somewhere else to sleep tonight.

263
00:20:41,820 --> 00:20:42,900
Here, Rome.

264
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:44,500
Got you a beer.

265
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:47,980
Thanks.

266
00:20:49,340 --> 00:20:50,660
Let's celebrate.

267
00:20:51,340 --> 00:20:52,540
It's going to be a long night.

268
00:20:52,780 --> 00:20:53,980
Cheers.

269
00:20:57,900 --> 00:20:59,980
Let me know if you need anything.
I've got you.

270
00:21:00,780 --> 00:21:03,900
Sleeping bag…
or some other kind of protection.

271
00:21:28,140 --> 00:21:29,660
Why aren't Tua and Arnold here yet?

272
00:21:30,380 --> 00:21:31,900
Don't tell me they're fighting harder?

273
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:35,540
Don't think so.

274
00:21:37,820 --> 00:21:39,140
Here they come.

275
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:53,980
So, have you two made up?

276
00:22:00,740 --> 00:22:01,740
If you have…

277
00:22:05,460 --> 00:22:06,579
Come here!

278
00:22:06,580 --> 00:22:07,580
Let's hit the water.

279
00:22:08,380 --> 00:22:10,100
Come! We've been waiting for you.

280
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:11,700
Get in the water.

281
00:22:11,820 --> 00:22:12,500
Let's go.

282
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:15,020
Come on, Tua.

283
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:32,300
Guys!

284
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:33,860
Why didn't you wait for me?

285
00:22:34,860 --> 00:22:36,940
Come.

286
00:22:37,740 --> 00:22:39,859
Jeez!

287
00:22:39,860 --> 00:22:41,780
So hot!

288
00:23:22,780 --> 00:23:25,179
Alright, everyone!

289
00:23:25,180 --> 00:23:26,180
Let's pause right here.

290
00:23:26,181 --> 00:23:27,580
Attention, attention!

291
00:23:27,820 --> 00:23:30,859
Stop talking and stop
drinking for a second.

292
00:23:30,860 --> 00:23:35,140
We've got a special performance
from the heads of our faculty play.

293
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:40,299
Jack, Tua, Dean, and Timmy!

294
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:45,859
Whoo!

295
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:47,779
Yay! Come on!

296
00:23:47,780 --> 00:23:49,620
Look at them. They're like a boy band!

297
00:24:11,260 --> 00:24:14,540
♪ Really liked when
you said the love word ♪

298
00:24:14,940 --> 00:24:17,860
♪ Haven't heard it in a long time ♪

299
00:24:18,380 --> 00:24:21,500
♪ Is it so hard to say it out loud? ♪

300
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:24,860
♪ Just say you still love me now ♪

301
00:24:25,540 --> 00:24:28,220
♪ I know your love is true ♪

302
00:24:29,060 --> 00:24:32,060
♪ I know that you still care ♪

303
00:24:32,580 --> 00:24:35,259
♪ I know it's not too hard to share ♪

304
00:24:35,260 --> 00:24:39,099
♪ Where's that same old word?
Wanna hear it again ♪

305
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:42,059
♪ Let's bring back the good old days ♪

306
00:24:42,060 --> 00:24:45,979
♪ Can you say, can you say,
Say it one more time? ♪

307
00:24:45,980 --> 00:24:49,099
♪ I've been wanting
to hear it for so long ♪

308
00:24:49,100 --> 00:24:53,219
♪ Can you say, can you say,
Say it one more time? ♪

309
00:24:53,220 --> 00:24:56,380
♪ Remind me that
your love is still strong ♪

310
00:24:56,980 --> 00:25:00,220
♪ Ja da da ja da da da da da ja ♪

311
00:25:15,260 --> 00:25:16,260
Awesome!

312
00:25:38,420 --> 00:25:39,740
I'm beat.

313
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:10,060
Do you want to spend the night with me?

314
00:26:10,780 --> 00:26:12,660
I'll have Raffy wait outside.

315
00:26:19,540 --> 00:26:21,660
No idea when I'll be done tonight.

316
00:26:22,540 --> 00:26:23,940
You should find someone else, Pete.

317
00:26:52,020 --> 00:26:54,740
I have solid evidence
of who embezzled the money.

318
00:27:11,060 --> 00:27:12,540
The sponsor gave us 200K.

319
00:27:13,380 --> 00:27:15,380
Why is there only 100K in the account?

320
00:27:17,772 --> 00:27:19,132
What are you talking about, Timmy?

321
00:27:30,583 --> 00:27:33,236
[Screenshot of a bank
transfer for 100k baht]

322
00:27:36,580 --> 00:27:38,300
This is one hell of a crappy job, Pete.

323
00:27:40,380 --> 00:27:41,580
How can you be this shameless?

324
00:27:42,060 --> 00:27:44,060
We busted our asses securing this sponsor.

325
00:27:44,660 --> 00:27:46,860
You didn't help at all,
and you're dragging us down.

326
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:49,900
I'm reporting this to the faculty board.

327
00:27:50,180 --> 00:27:51,540
You'll be expelled.

328
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:53,340
You won't graduate.

329
00:27:53,900 --> 00:27:55,380
And I'm taking this to the police.

330
00:27:55,940 --> 00:27:57,500
Let's not involve the police.

331
00:27:57,873 --> 00:27:59,912
Timmy, please.

332
00:28:00,060 --> 00:28:01,140
Don't go to the police.

333
00:28:01,740 --> 00:28:02,740
Please, Jack.

334
00:28:08,300 --> 00:28:09,540
Then return the money soon.

335
00:28:11,140 --> 00:28:13,860
Or you're kicked out of the project.

336
00:28:16,652 --> 00:28:19,892
We should rename
Romeo &amp; Romeo to Prison Break.

337
00:28:23,047 --> 00:28:24,127
And remember this,

338
00:28:24,980 --> 00:28:28,540
I won't let this play fail,
no matter what the fuck happens.

339
00:28:41,693 --> 00:28:42,693
Jack.

340
00:28:44,279 --> 00:28:45,319
What are you doing here?

341
00:28:46,613 --> 00:28:47,613
Are you okay?

342
00:28:49,700 --> 00:28:50,700
I'm okay.

343
00:28:55,780 --> 00:28:57,660
And right now…

344
00:29:00,340 --> 00:29:01,740
I'm feeling just right.

345
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:09,620
You said you'd go running with me tomorrow.

346
00:29:10,180 --> 00:29:11,460
I don't think you'll be able to.

347
00:29:12,340 --> 00:29:13,460
I will.

348
00:29:15,180 --> 00:29:21,420
With you, whether it's an obstacle race
or a marathon, I can handle anything.

349
00:29:26,660 --> 00:29:31,260
But right now, can you spend time with me?

350
00:29:37,300 --> 00:29:38,300
No.

351
00:29:42,060 --> 00:29:43,460
I don't like myself when I'm drunk.

352
00:29:45,140 --> 00:29:46,220
And you are too.

353
00:29:47,380 --> 00:29:48,420
You should get some sleep.

354
00:29:49,700 --> 00:29:53,420
Hey, if I wanted to sleep,
I could've stayed home.

355
00:30:01,540 --> 00:30:03,140
You don't look like you can go on.

356
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:07,459
Come on, I'll walk you back to the tent.

357
00:30:07,460 --> 00:30:08,980
No.

358
00:30:10,020 --> 00:30:11,820
I'm fine. Don't worry about me.

359
00:30:12,420 --> 00:30:13,580
I can find my way back.

360
00:30:14,700 --> 00:30:18,020
Besides, it's our last year.

361
00:30:19,080 --> 00:30:20,560
I want to enjoy it while I can.

362
00:30:22,453 --> 00:30:23,453
Mm.

363
00:30:24,340 --> 00:30:26,060
If you want to go all in, that's your call.

364
00:30:26,780 --> 00:30:28,140
But are you sure you've got this?

365
00:30:31,860 --> 00:30:32,860
I am.

366
00:30:51,340 --> 00:30:52,500
I knew it.

367
00:30:56,420 --> 00:30:57,420
Sorry.

368
00:31:06,060 --> 00:31:07,060
Hey.

369
00:31:08,540 --> 00:31:12,580
Thanks a lot, Arnold, for forgiving me.

370
00:31:13,540 --> 00:31:18,180
I know I w as wrong,
but I don't want you to think that way.

371
00:31:19,267 --> 00:31:21,467
I did it because I truly meant well.

372
00:31:22,660 --> 00:31:23,660
And…

373
00:31:24,346 --> 00:31:25,626
I wanted to spend time with you.

374
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:29,500
Tua, you've said that
like a hundred times already.

375
00:31:29,980 --> 00:31:31,556
I get it. You don't have to say it again.

376
00:31:31,580 --> 00:31:33,380
You keep repeating yourself
when you're drunk.

377
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:37,100
And I'll keep saying it.

378
00:31:38,013 --> 00:31:41,013
Because I'm happy to have you in my life.

379
00:31:48,380 --> 00:31:50,060
Yeah, you're totally drunk.

380
00:31:50,460 --> 00:31:52,340
Let me take you back to the tent.

381
00:31:55,740 --> 00:31:58,300
Tua! Arnold!

382
00:31:59,140 --> 00:32:00,140
Dean!

383
00:32:00,500 --> 00:32:03,020
I'm so glad you guys made up.

384
00:32:04,060 --> 00:32:05,700
Don't fight again.

385
00:32:05,900 --> 00:32:06,900
Got it?

386
00:32:07,020 --> 00:32:08,500
Yeah, we're good.

387
00:32:08,980 --> 00:32:09,900
Love each other.

388
00:32:09,901 --> 00:32:12,140
Yeah, we love each other.

389
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:15,380
You're drunk, Dean.

390
00:32:16,436 --> 00:32:18,915
Drunk? This much alcohol can't touch me.

391
00:32:18,940 --> 00:32:20,459
It's nothing.

392
00:32:20,460 --> 00:32:21,340
Whoa!
Let me show you.

393
00:32:25,780 --> 00:32:26,300
Hey!

394
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:29,740
Jeez!

395
00:32:31,980 --> 00:32:32,980
You're awesome.

396
00:32:33,100 --> 00:32:34,100
That was nothing.

397
00:32:34,500 --> 00:32:36,780
Dean, what are you doing here?

398
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:38,100
Come.

399
00:32:38,101 --> 00:32:39,659
Are you going to throw up?

400
00:32:39,660 --> 00:32:40,460
I'm not throwing up.

401
00:32:40,461 --> 00:32:42,020
Come with us.

402
00:32:42,180 --> 00:32:43,780
Hey, you two. Love each other.

403
00:32:44,660 --> 00:32:45,660
Love each other.

404
00:32:45,980 --> 00:32:46,980
Oops.

405
00:32:47,860 --> 00:32:48,660
You almost let me fall.

406
00:32:48,661 --> 00:32:50,020
Dude, it's just grass.

407
00:32:51,020 --> 00:32:52,380
Come on, bottoms up.

408
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:54,460
Then I'll take you to bed.

409
00:33:18,300 --> 00:33:19,300
Whoo!

410
00:33:19,980 --> 00:33:20,980
Come on.

411
00:33:22,340 --> 00:33:24,380
Yay!

412
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:30,180
Come on. Down the hatch.
Yep.

413
00:33:35,420 --> 00:33:36,420
No.

414
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:37,500
I don't want it.

415
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:41,540
Just for fun. Come here.

416
00:33:42,620 --> 00:33:43,620
Oh, gosh.

417
00:33:54,860 --> 00:33:57,780
Whoo!

418
00:34:32,940 --> 00:34:34,260
Tua. Hey.

419
00:34:35,260 --> 00:34:37,420
Why don't you change first?
You'll be more comfortable.

420
00:34:37,580 --> 00:34:38,580
Look at you.

421
00:34:40,660 --> 00:34:41,660
Fine, I'll do it.

422
00:35:01,100 --> 00:35:04,100
After this trip,
it's your turn to take care of me.

423
00:35:04,660 --> 00:35:05,940
Buy me a meal.

424
00:35:27,340 --> 00:35:31,100
I'm glad to have you in my life.

425
00:36:15,500 --> 00:36:16,500
My phone…

426
00:36:43,860 --> 00:36:46,740
MEET ME OUTSIDE.

427
00:37:52,820 --> 00:37:53,820
I saw you.

428
00:37:54,626 --> 00:37:56,026
You still haven't given up on Jack?

429
00:37:58,566 --> 00:38:02,246
I'm sure Jack and Dean
will definitely get back together.

430
00:38:03,900 --> 00:38:04,900
Damn right.

431
00:38:05,326 --> 00:38:06,766
Dean made that very clear.

432
00:38:09,260 --> 00:38:10,740
But stay the hell out of my business.

433
00:38:13,300 --> 00:38:14,300
Now what?

434
00:38:15,340 --> 00:38:16,740
Want me to call Pete over?

435
00:38:17,513 --> 00:38:18,513
Go ahead.

436
00:38:18,833 --> 00:38:20,433
You've been pushing us together all day.

437
00:38:20,693 --> 00:38:21,693
Call him.

438
00:38:21,893 --> 00:38:22,893
I'll take him.

439
00:38:24,060 --> 00:38:25,900
Fine. I'll go get him.

440
00:38:31,380 --> 00:38:34,620
If I really do take
him, you'll get jealous.

441
00:38:35,313 --> 00:38:36,313
You already like me.

442
00:38:37,460 --> 00:38:38,460
Why play games?

443
00:38:40,287 --> 00:38:41,287
So?

444
00:38:42,060 --> 00:38:43,420
I'm annoying like that.

445
00:38:45,686 --> 00:38:46,846
If you can handle that, stay.

446
00:38:48,133 --> 00:38:49,133
If not, walk away.

447
00:38:52,020 --> 00:38:53,780
Someone like you…

448
00:38:55,453 --> 00:38:56,773
is exactly my type.

449
00:38:57,807 --> 00:39:01,647
The harder you play,
the softer you'll be for me.

450
00:39:03,660 --> 00:39:04,660
You're all talk.

451
00:39:06,340 --> 00:39:07,380
Do it already.

452
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:10,200
See?

453
00:39:10,653 --> 00:39:14,213
You and I both want it.

454
00:40:29,420 --> 00:40:30,699
Arnold!

455
00:40:30,700 --> 00:40:33,340
Oops, sorry.

456
00:40:33,780 --> 00:40:35,700
- Dean.
- Sorry.

457
00:40:35,980 --> 00:40:36,980
You okay?

458
00:40:37,500 --> 00:40:38,500
I'm good.

459
00:40:39,180 --> 00:40:40,180
Where's Tua?

460
00:40:40,420 --> 00:40:41,420
Asleep.

461
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:44,460
Gosh. Such a lightweight.

462
00:40:45,620 --> 00:40:46,620
What about you?

463
00:40:47,500 --> 00:40:49,060
Hope you're not a lightweight like him.

464
00:40:52,780 --> 00:40:55,140
Here. Let me test that.

465
00:40:56,620 --> 00:40:57,620
Yeah?

466
00:40:58,180 --> 00:40:58,980
Bring it on.
Come on.

467
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:06,300
Whoa, Dean!

468
00:41:07,220 --> 00:41:08,780
That's so strong.

469
00:41:10,420 --> 00:41:11,500
That's right.

470
00:41:11,740 --> 00:41:14,940
My Romeo's got to be this strong.

471
00:41:18,020 --> 00:41:20,380
Yay!

472
00:41:23,620 --> 00:41:25,180
Cute moment.

473
00:41:25,460 --> 00:41:28,580
Can we get some photos? We need content.

474
00:41:31,060 --> 00:41:37,780
Make everyone smile so wide it hurts—
They'll be searching #DentalClinicNearMe.

475
00:41:38,740 --> 00:41:40,180
Alright then.

476
00:41:43,300 --> 00:41:47,899
A cheek kiss.

477
00:41:47,900 --> 00:41:50,220
Please.

478
00:41:50,580 --> 00:41:53,020
Okay. Snap it.

479
00:41:53,740 --> 00:41:55,179
One, two, three.

480
00:41:55,180 --> 00:41:58,100
Aww!

481
00:41:58,900 --> 00:42:00,499
Wait.

482
00:42:00,500 --> 00:42:01,540
I didn't press the button.

483
00:42:02,500 --> 00:42:05,259
One more.

484
00:42:05,260 --> 00:42:06,260
No!

485
00:42:08,260 --> 00:42:09,900
No more.

486
00:42:10,500 --> 00:42:11,780
I'm not doing it.

487
00:42:12,820 --> 00:42:13,780
No!
Let's go, Arnold.

488
00:42:18,300 --> 00:42:19,420
Hurry up.

489
00:42:19,660 --> 00:42:20,700
Where are we going?

490
00:42:31,420 --> 00:42:36,900
Hey, you know I'm really glad
Tua suggested you act with me?

491
00:42:37,180 --> 00:42:40,500
I think we have great acting chemistry.

492
00:42:41,620 --> 00:42:43,380
I should be thanking you too.

493
00:42:44,100 --> 00:42:45,220
You're so talented.

494
00:42:45,460 --> 00:42:48,780
You set the bar high, so I have to keep up.

495
00:42:49,100 --> 00:42:50,819
Of course. I'm top-tier in this faculty.

496
00:42:50,820 --> 00:42:54,060
Wow, the drunker you get,
the more confident you are.

497
00:42:54,220 --> 00:42:54,940
Naturally.

498
00:42:55,140 --> 00:42:58,459
I'm Dean, Prince of Fine Arts.

499
00:42:58,460 --> 00:42:59,780
Gosh!

500
00:43:00,860 --> 00:43:02,219
Alright, Prince of Fine Arts.

501
00:43:02,220 --> 00:43:03,220
You almost collapsed.

502
00:43:04,700 --> 00:43:06,060
I almost did.

503
00:43:09,140 --> 00:43:12,140
Is this for content too?

504
00:43:12,660 --> 00:43:13,660
Where's the camera?

505
00:43:16,020 --> 00:43:17,020
No camera.

506
00:43:17,740 --> 00:43:18,740
Just me.

507
00:43:20,500 --> 00:43:21,500
Okay.

508
00:43:54,980 --> 00:43:59,740
Romeo, I want to stay with you tonight.

509
00:44:00,140 --> 00:44:01,180
Can I?

510
00:44:04,500 --> 00:44:09,100
We should head back
before someone sees us, Romeo.

511
00:44:19,580 --> 00:44:23,500
When we get to the tent,
you go in first. I'll follow after.

512
00:44:24,900 --> 00:44:25,900
Why?

513
00:44:26,780 --> 00:44:28,020
So Pete doesn't get suspicious.

514
00:44:37,500 --> 00:44:39,540
Hey, where are you going?

515
00:45:42,660 --> 00:45:43,980
Jack, Jack, hold on.

516
00:45:45,100 --> 00:45:46,100
Let me catch my breath.

517
00:45:46,540 --> 00:45:47,540
I'm tired.

518
00:45:50,580 --> 00:45:51,580
Are you alright?

519
00:45:56,380 --> 00:45:59,060
I told you I'd wake up to run with you.

520
00:46:04,086 --> 00:46:05,926
You've really changed.

521
00:46:06,820 --> 00:46:08,180
The old you wouldn't even get up.

522
00:46:13,740 --> 00:46:16,740
I told you I'd change.

523
00:46:26,780 --> 00:46:27,380
Hello?

524
00:46:27,381 --> 00:46:28,739
(Hi, son.)

525
00:46:28,740 --> 00:46:30,380
(Have you talked to your sister lately?)

526
00:46:31,020 --> 00:46:32,620
Not at all, Mom. Why?

527
00:46:33,100 --> 00:46:34,620
(Her boyfriend hit her again.)

528
00:46:34,839 --> 00:46:36,519
(It was a bad fight this time.)

529
00:46:36,706 --> 00:46:37,706
(I'm really worried.)

530
00:46:38,140 --> 00:46:39,900
(But I can't leave work to go to Bangkok.)

531
00:46:40,220 --> 00:46:42,500
(If you have time,
can you check on her for me?)

532
00:46:43,140 --> 00:46:44,340
Sure.

533
00:46:45,300 --> 00:46:46,460
I'll go check on her.

534
00:46:54,846 --> 00:46:55,846
Is something wrong?

535
00:47:01,060 --> 00:47:02,180
My big sister.

536
00:47:02,460 --> 00:47:04,140
She moved to Bangkok with her boyfriend.

537
00:47:04,633 --> 00:47:05,833
At first, everything was fine.

538
00:47:06,500 --> 00:47:08,660
But later, whenever they fight,
it turns physical.

539
00:47:10,260 --> 00:47:12,620
Mom and I have been telling her
to leave him, but she won't.

540
00:47:13,460 --> 00:47:14,780
This time must be serious.

541
00:47:15,820 --> 00:47:17,380
Otherwise, Mom wouldn't have called me.

542
00:47:21,600 --> 00:47:24,080
If there's anything I can do, let me know.

543
00:47:28,820 --> 00:47:32,140
It's okay. It's a family
issue. I'll handle it.

544
00:47:37,460 --> 00:47:38,460
Dean.

545
00:47:40,660 --> 00:47:43,660
Your issues are my issues.

546
00:48:01,300 --> 00:48:02,300
Let's keep going.

547
00:48:13,700 --> 00:48:14,860
Guess I have to admit it.

548
00:48:16,420 --> 00:48:17,900
I do want to take care of him.

549
00:48:35,860 --> 00:48:37,660
Look at you. Are you good?

550
00:48:38,380 --> 00:48:40,636
You should have something hot.
It'll help with the hangover.

551
00:48:40,660 --> 00:48:42,940
Hey, they have congee too?

552
00:48:43,246 --> 00:48:44,926
I asked the staff to make it.

553
00:48:45,660 --> 00:48:47,140
It should help you feel better.

554
00:48:50,620 --> 00:48:51,620
Thank you.

555
00:48:53,460 --> 00:48:54,460
Eat with me.

556
00:48:54,700 --> 00:48:56,356
It's okay. I don't want to take your food.

557
00:48:56,380 --> 00:48:57,380
Eat with me.

558
00:48:57,740 --> 00:48:58,940
You're hungover too.

559
00:48:59,140 --> 00:49:01,260
Besides, it tastes better
when we eat together.

560
00:49:18,740 --> 00:49:21,420
Guys, look at that!

561
00:49:21,580 --> 00:49:26,220
The old place brings
together the old flames.

562
00:49:27,380 --> 00:49:30,820
They can't cut each other off
because they're meant to be together.

563
00:49:31,940 --> 00:49:32,940
Because they're what?

564
00:49:33,180 --> 00:49:36,100
Meant to be together!

565
00:49:36,940 --> 00:49:37,940
Don't overthink it.

566
00:49:38,460 --> 00:49:39,540
They're just teasing.

567
00:49:45,620 --> 00:49:46,620
Dean and I…

568
00:49:48,140 --> 00:49:49,380
we're getting back together.

569
00:49:54,700 --> 00:49:56,739
Yay!

570
00:49:56,740 --> 00:49:59,059
See?

571
00:49:59,060 --> 00:50:00,940
You heard that?

572
00:50:04,460 --> 00:50:07,419
Watch out for the ants over there.

573
00:50:07,420 --> 00:50:08,780
It's getting way too sweet.

574
00:50:10,580 --> 00:50:12,020
I knew it.

575
00:50:12,140 --> 00:50:14,740
You two can't escape each other.

576
00:50:15,420 --> 00:50:19,420
If this play flops, I'm
cursing you two for life.

577
00:50:20,700 --> 00:50:21,700
It's alright.

578
00:50:22,060 --> 00:50:24,740
Right now, the whole
mountain is still pink.

579
00:50:35,180 --> 00:50:36,180
Let's do it.

580
00:50:36,572 --> 00:50:37,572
Call it a fresh start.

581
00:51:28,460 --> 00:51:31,420
(Next Episode) You exposed Dean
as a host before, did it even affect him?

582
00:51:31,940 --> 00:51:33,940
So you're just going to
let those two off the hook?

583
00:51:34,020 --> 00:51:36,100
Don't think nobody
notices what you're doing.

584
00:51:36,500 --> 00:51:37,619
You'd better be careful.

585
00:51:37,620 --> 00:51:40,460
I really want to know
how Jack would see you…

586
00:51:42,580 --> 00:51:43,580
if he found out.

587
00:51:45,180 --> 00:51:47,140
Happy three-year anniversary.

588
00:51:47,580 --> 00:51:48,740
Will you marry me?

589
00:51:50,620 --> 00:51:52,340
Will you quit playing around?

590
00:51:53,780 --> 00:51:59,060
If we're still together in the future,
I'd want to get married.

591
00:51:59,860 --> 00:52:03,060
Now it's clear to you
how we feel about each other.

592
00:52:05,460 --> 00:52:07,460
But I want to make it clearer.
